<br>
1)  Empty server.  I can actually hunt freely and often get a few mobs I desire.<br>
2)  TLC.  I love it.  The challenge of HAVING to kill a mob while it is still a danger to you to complete quests, to have to plan in advance.  On blue servers, you find most people completing quests when the mobs are green and easy.  I'm currently completing my iceforged shackles quest at level 40 ... the danger is there .. so is the thrill of victory.<br>
3)  Starting untwinked.  Characters have earnt all gear.  No random people handing out 'junk' drops from level 50 mobs.   I feel proud of my Gatorscale leggings, my sentry gaunts, my crystal belt .. all earnt.  My Saryrn Ranger has very nice gear, I do not feel proud about any item but the 'ice forged shackles' he has (soloed at 51).<br>
4)  My guild.  Started in a small guild that raids once a week and has fun doing it.  We are able to chose a destination and we normally find it uncamped.  We raid locations way above our level and have a lot of fun doing so.  This cannot be done anywhere else.<br>
5)  Roleplay.  I sometimes roleplay when I get into a pickup group.<br>
6)  A lack of annoying tells to my druid for ports (well, in comparison to Saryrn anyhow).<br>
7)  I have made a few good friends on the server.  Nice people, some are even roleplayers! (To Roleplay police - God forbid they know someone called 'Baldisking' who does not use 'thees' or 'thous' - ban them now, and me for that matter!).<br>
<br>
Dislike:<br>
<br>
1) Lack of groups.<br>
2) Lack of common sense in many players.  Often an ability to run to zone at the sight of ..... 2 mobs being pulled to a group of 6 <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   'BraveSirRobin' should be many peoples surnames on this server.  A guildy has once asked jokingly if the Ranger in his group who ran on the sight of ..... ONE gnoll! ... was roleplaying a coward.<br>
3) Roleplay Police.  Sorry, I dont use thees and thous.  you dont like it. Well, do not presume to announce across /shout and other mediums that I should obey your way of playing.  /shout can be ignored by yourself (I rarely use it anyhow).  Basically get a life and play your own game and do not interfere with mine. I do roleplay and in many ways better than yourselves. I have 2 characters both with follical impediments and their own traits.  This is a roleplay 'Preferred Server' anyhow and also where in gods name does it state 'use olde english'?. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/urubisthenome.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rubis the Nome</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 40<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/21/02 11:31:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1429.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What do you like about FV and what do you dislike</span><hr size=1> Inkie was a term used by roleplaying Trolls and Ogres back int he day pre kunark.  When used by a troll using troll talk it really fits, but I have personally never heard the word drow used.  On the other hand the general DE greetings I have been hearing I ahve also never heard off this server.  /shrug <p><p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=373025>Rubis<BR></p></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utzarothfv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tzaroth FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 522<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/21/02 11:49:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1429.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </t